Aliases: multiple myeloma and other plasma cell neoplasms

C0024348.Name: Lysis
C0024348.Definition: Tissue structure disintegration and destruction due to action of endogenous or/and exogenous lytic substances which include but not limited to naturally occurring or laboratory designed proteolytic enzymes, glycosidases, detergents, pore-forming proteins, immune complexes, etc. Tissue lysis plays role in pathogenesis of a number of conditions e.g. protozoal infections, ischemic tissue injury, and autoimmune disorders. It is also used as a basis for non-surgical treatment modality to remove or minimize presence of abnormal tissue, e.g. adhesions.

C0032284.Name: Pneumonectomy
C0032284.Definition: The excision of lung tissue including partial or total lung lobectomy.

C0038638.Name: Suction drainage
C0038638.Definition: The removal of secretions, gas or fluid from hollow or tubular organs or cavities by means of a tube and a device that acts on negative pressure.

C0001613.Name: Adrenal Cortex
C0001613.Definition: The outer layer of the adrenal gland. It is derived from MESODERM and comprised of three zones (outer ZONA GLOMERULOSA, middle ZONA FASCICULATA, and inner ZONA RETICULARIS) with each producing various steroids preferentially, such as ALDOSTERONE; HYDROCORTISONE; DEHYDROEPIANDROSTERONE; and ANDROSTENEDIONE. Adrenal cortex function is regulated by pituitary ADRENOCORTICOTROPIN.

C0010709.Name: Cyst
C0010709.Definition: Any fluid-filled closed cavity or sac that is lined by an EPITHELIUM. Cysts can be of normal, abnormal, non-neoplastic, or neoplastic tissues.

C2003903.Name: Profiling (action)
C2003903.Definition: An analysis (often in graphical form) representing the extent to which something exhibits various characteristics.

C0972401.Name: Boards (medical device)
C0972401.Definition: Flat, usually rectangular, pieces of material (e.g., wood, plastic) that have appropriate physical characteristics (e.g., strength) and dimensions for a particular clinical use.

C1516048.Name: Assessed
C1516048.Definition: The final result of a determination of the value, significance, or extent of.

C0013819.Name: Electroencephalography
C0013819.Definition: Recording of electric currents developed in the brain by means of electrodes applied to the scalp, to the surface of the brain, or placed within the substance of the brain.

C0439228.Name: day
C0439228.Definition: The time for Earth to make a complete rotation on its axis; ordinarily divided into twenty-four hours, equal to 86 400 seconds. This also refers to a specific day.

C0230132.Name: Anterior chest wall structure
C0230132.Definition: Subdivision of thorax which is anterior to the plane of the posterior boundary of the middle mediastinum. Examples: There is only one anterior chest.
Aliases: structure of surface region of front of chest
structure of surface region of front of chest (body structure)
surface region of front of chest

C0349590.Name: Nature
C0349590.Definition: The system of all phenomena in space and time; the totality of physical reality. It is both a scientific and philosophic concept appearing in all historic eras. (Webster 2d; Dr. James H. Cassedy, NLM History of Medicine Division)

C0040132.Name: Thyroid Gland
C0040132.Definition: A highly vascularized endocrine gland consisting of two lobes joined by a thin band of tissue with one lobe on each side of the TRACHEA. It secretes THYROID HORMONES from the follicular cells and CALCITONIN from the parafollicular cells thereby regulating METABOLISM and CALCIUM level in blood, respectively.

C0029433.Name: Osteogenesis
C0029433.Definition: The process of bone formation. Histogenesis of bone including ossification.

C0332501.Name: Spherical shape
C0332501.Definition: A solid or hollow three-dimensional object bounded by a closed surface such that every point on the surface is equidistant from the center.

C1313915.Name: Redundancy
C1313915.Definition: The attribute of being superfluous and unneeded.

C0023685.Name: Ligaments
C0023685.Definition: Shiny, flexible bands of fibrous tissue connecting together articular extremities of bones. They are pliant, tough, and inextensile.

C1550452.Name: definition - ActMoodCompletionTrack
C1550452.Definition: Definition:A definition of a kind of act that can occur .OpenIssue:The semantic constructs embodied in DEF and CRT moods seem indistinguishable, and their uses can readily be determined by the context in which these are used. Therefore, this OpenIssue has been created to declare that it is likely that ActMood.DEF will be "retired" in the future in favor of the more general ActMood.CRT.

C0205054.Name: Hepatic
C0205054.Definition: Pertaining to, affecting, or associated with the liver.

C0001861.Name: Air (substance)
C0001861.Definition: The mixture of gases present in the earth's atmosphere consisting of oxygen, nitrogen, carbon dioxide, and small amounts of other gases.

C0039503.Name: Tendinitis
C0039503.Definition: Inflammation of a tendon, usually resulting from an overuse injury. It is characterized by swelling of the tendon, tenderness around the inflamed tendon, and pain while moving the affected area of the body.

C0005775.Name: Blood Circulation
C0005775.Definition: The movement of the BLOOD as it is pumped through the CARDIOVASCULAR SYSTEM.

C0006277.Name: Bronchitis
C0006277.Definition: Inflammation of the large airways in the lung including any part of the BRONCHI, from the PRIMARY BRONCHI to the TERTIARY BRONCHI.
Aliases: bronchitis, not specified as acute or chronic

C0230185.Name: Epigastrium
C0230185.Definition: The upper central region of the abdomen between the costal margins and the subcostal plane.

C0744743.Name: Hemiarthroplasty
C0744743.Definition: A partial joint replacement in which only one surface of the joint is replaced with a PROSTHESIS.

C0020492.Name: Hyperostosis
C0020492.Definition: Increase in the mass of bone per unit volume.

C0034599.Name: Radiology Specialty
C0034599.Definition: A specialty concerned with the use of x-ray and other forms of radiant energy in the diagnosis and treatment of disease.

C1708056.Name: Fiducial
C1708056.Definition: Used as a fixed standard of reference for comparison or measurement.

C0729936.Name: Cardiac chamber structure
C0729936.Definition: Organ chamber which consists of a wall that surrounds the cavity of a cardiac atrium or ventricle.

C0001246.Name: Actinium
C0001246.Definition: A trivalent radioactive element and the prototypical member of the actinide family. It has the atomic symbol Ac, and atomic number 89. Its principal isotope is 227 and it decays primarily by beta-emission.

C0013227.Name: Pharmaceutical Preparations
C0013227.Definition: Drugs intended for human or veterinary use, presented in their finished dosage form. Included here are materials used in the preparation and/or formulation of the finished dosage form.

C0231218.Name: Malaise
C0231218.Definition: A feeling of general discomfort or uneasiness, an out-of-sorts feeling.

C0443196.Name: Definitive
C0443196.Definition: Supplying or being a final or conclusive settlement or result.

C0522510.Name: With intensity
C0522510.Definition: The degree or magnitude of strength, energy, or feeling.

C0008114.Name: Chin
C0008114.Definition: The anatomical frontal portion of the mandible, also known as the mentum, that contains the line of fusion of the two separate halves of the mandible (symphysis menti). This line of fusion divides inferiorly to enclose a triangular area called the mental protuberance. On each side, inferior to the second premolar tooth, is the mental foramen for the passage of blood vessels and a nerve.

C0038999.Name: Swelling
C0038999.Definition: Enlargement; expansion in size; sign of inflammation

C0014243.Name: Endoscopes
C0014243.Definition: Instruments for the visual examination of interior structures of the body. There are rigid endoscopes and flexible fiberoptic endoscopes for various types of viewing in ENDOSCOPY.

C0439534.Name: Dimensions
C0439534.Definition: The magnitude of something in a particular direction, especially length or width or height.

C1947910.Name: Pulse phenomenon
C1947910.Definition: Any of a series of intermittent occurrences characterized by a brief, sudden change in a quantity.

C0439849.Name: Relationships
C0439849.Definition: A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something.

C0002808.Name: Science of Anatomy
C0002808.Definition: A branch of biology dealing with the structure of organisms.

C0237881.Name: Statistical Significance
C0237881.Definition: In statistics, a number that expresses the probability that the result of a given experiment or study could have occurred purely by chance. This number can be a margin of error or it can indicate a confidence level.

C0543419.Name: Sequela of disorder
C0543419.Definition: A pathologic condition that results from a disease, treatment, or injury.

C0022646.Name: Kidney
C0022646.Definition: Body organ that filters blood for the secretion of URINE and that regulates ion concentrations.

C0487742.Name: Width
C0487742.Definition: The extent or measurement of something from side to side.

C0002978.Name: angiogram
C0002978.Definition: Radiography of blood vessels after injection of a contrast medium.

C0034519.Name: Electromagnetic Radiation
C0034519.Definition: Waves of oscillating electric and MAGNETIC FIELDS which move at right angles to each other and outward from the source.

C0444598.Name: Middle
C0444598.Definition: An intermediate part or section; an area that is approximately central within some larger region.

C1444754.Name: Length
C1444754.Definition: The linear extent in space from one end of something to the other end, or the extent of something from beginning to end.

C0450123.Name: Tracheobronchial
C0450123.Definition: Pertaining both to the tracheal and bronchial tubes, or to their junction.

C0684224.Name: Report (document)
C0684224.Definition: Detailed account or statement or formal record of the proceedings of a meeting or session. May also document status or progress of an activity or research project.

C0544726.Name: Hole Finding
C0544726.Definition: An aperture or hollow space within a solid mass

C0027551.Name: Needle device
C0027551.Definition: Sharp instruments used for puncturing or suturing.

C1708264.Name: Guidewire Device
C1708264.Definition: A flexible wire designed to help position medical devices within the body.

C1314939.Name: Involvement with
C1314939.Definition: To have a connection by participation or association or use; sharing in an activity or process.

C2700618.Name: Cavitation (process)
C2700618.Definition: The formation and rapid collapse of bubbles in a fluid. The creation of bubbles is driven by mechanical force.

C0030193.Name: Pain
C0030193.Definition: An unpleasant sensation induced by noxious stimuli which are detected by NERVE ENDINGS of NOCICEPTIVE NEURONS.

C1280500.Name: Effect
C1280500.Definition: A phenomenon that follows and is caused by some previous phenomenon.

C0557702.Name: Window (physical object)
C0557702.Definition: A part of a computer screen that contains a display different from the rest of the screen.

C1282913.Name: Circular
C1282913.Definition: A ring-shaped structure with every point equidistant from the center.

C0024299.Name: Lymphoma
C0024299.Definition: A general term for various neoplastic diseases of the lymphoid tissue.

C0031354.Name: Pharyngeal structure
C0031354.Definition: A funnel-shaped fibromuscular tube that conducts food to the ESOPHAGUS, and air to the LARYNX and LUNGS. It is located posterior to the NASAL CAVITY; ORAL CAVITY; and LARYNX, and extends from the SKULL BASE to the inferior border of the CRICOID CARTILAGE anteriorly and to the inferior border of the C6 vertebra posteriorly. It is divided into the NASOPHARYNX; OROPHARYNX; and HYPOPHARYNX (laryngopharynx).

C0040811.Name: Trees (plant)
C0040811.Definition: Woody, usually tall, perennial higher plants (Angiosperms, Gymnosperms, and some Pterophyta) having usually a main stem and numerous branches.

C1880791.Name: Flexure
C1880791.Definition: An angular or rounded shape made by folding.

C1510776.Name: Addendum
C1510776.Definition: An appendage to an existing document that contains supplemental information. The parent document remains content is unaltered.

C0009678.Name: Congenital MeSH qualifier
C0009678.Definition: Used with disease headings to indicate those conditions existing at, and usually before, birth. It excludes morphologic abnormalities and birth injuries, for which "abnormalities" and "injuries" are used.

C0040452.Name: Tooth root structure
C0040452.Definition: The part of a tooth from the neck to the apex, embedded in the alveolar process and covered with cementum. A root may be single or divided into several branches, usually identified by their relative position, e.g., lingual root or buccal root. Single-rooted teeth include mandibular first and second premolars and the maxillary second premolar teeth. The maxillary first premolar has two roots in most cases. Maxillary molars have three roots. (Jablonski, Dictionary of Dentistry, 1992, p690)

C0456205.Name: Contents
C0456205.Definition: Everything that is included in a collection, container, or communication.

C0040594.Name: Track (course)
C0040594.Definition: A course artificially laid out for running or racing

C0332261.Name: Spreading (qualifier value)
C0332261.Definition: The act of extending over a wider scope or expanse of space or time.

C0007301.Name: Cartilage
C0007301.Definition: A non-vascular form of connective tissue composed of CHONDROCYTES embedded in a matrix that includes CHONDROITIN SULFATE and various types of FIBRILLAR COLLAGEN. There are three major types: HYALINE CARTILAGE; FIBROCARTILAGE; and ELASTIC CARTILAGE.

C0007272.Name: Carotid Arteries
C0007272.Definition: Either of the two principal arteries on both sides of the neck that supply blood to the head and neck; each divides into two branches, the internal carotid artery and the external carotid artery.

C0006290.Name: Bronchoscopy
C0006290.Definition: Endoscopic examination, therapy or surgery of the bronchi.

C4684445.Name: Delineate
C4684445.Definition: To describe something precisely or to indicate the exact position of a boundary or border.

C0205374.Name: Transitory
C0205374.Definition: Not permanent; not lasting; lacking continuity or regularity.

C0392752.Name: Localized
C0392752.Definition: Being confined or restricted to a particular location. [HPO:probinson]

C1308727.Name: RBBP8 protein, human
C1308727.Definition: Retinoblastoma binding protein 8 (897 aa, ~102 kDa) is encoded by the human RBBP8 gene. This protein is involved in cell cycle checkpoint control.
Aliases: sporulation in the absence of spo11 protein 2 homolog

C4055270.Name: Cardiothoracic
C4055270.Definition: Relating to the heart and chest.

C0034896.Name: Rectum
C0034896.Definition: The distal segment of the LARGE INTESTINE, between the SIGMOID COLON and the ANAL CANAL.

C0032699.Name: Porifera
C0032699.Definition: The phylum of sponges which are sessile, suspension-feeding, multicellular animals that utilize flagellated cells called choanocytes to circulate water. Most are hermaphroditic. They are probably an early evolutionary side branch that gave rise to no other group of animals. Except for about 150 freshwater species, sponges are marine animals. They are a source of ALKALOIDS; STEROLS; and other complex molecules useful in medicine and biological research.

C0027540.Name: Necrosis
C0027540.Definition: The death of cells in an organ or tissue due to disease, injury or failure of the blood supply.

C0460005.Name: Trunk structure
C0460005.Definition: The central part of the body to which the neck and limbs are attached.

C0003086.Name: Ankle
C0003086.Definition: The region of the lower limb between the FOOT and the LEG.

C0005767.Name: Blood
C0005767.Definition: The body fluid that circulates in the vascular system (BLOOD VESSELS). Whole blood includes PLASMA and BLOOD CELLS.

C3272911.Name: Radiodensity
C3272911.Definition: The transparency of a material to the passage of X-rays and other forms of radiation.

C0029355.Name: Orthopedics
C0029355.Definition: A specialty which utilizes medical, surgical, and physical methods to treat and correct deformities, diseases, and injuries to the skeletal system, its articulations, and associated structures.

C0344315.Name: Depressed mood
C0344315.Definition: An emotional state characterized by feelings of sadness, emptiness, and/or tearfulness.

C0080078.Name: Range of Motion, Articular
C0080078.Definition: The distance and direction to which a bone joint can be extended. Range of motion is a function of the condition of the joints, muscles, and connective tissues involved. Joint flexibility can be improved through appropriate MUSCLE STRETCHING EXERCISES.

C1706765.Name: Alignment
C1706765.Definition: The act of adjusting or aligning objects in relation to each other; the result of this activity.

C1522634.Name: Question (inquiry)
C1522634.Definition: A sentence of inquiry that asks for a reply; a request for information (e.g., a formal request to a database or search engine).

C0162326.Name: DNA Sequence
C0162326.Definition: The sequence of nucleotide residues along a DNA chain.

C1881065.Name: Homogeneity
C1881065.Definition: The quality or state of being similar or comparable in kind or nature or of being uniform throughout in composition or structure.

C0444454.Name: Access
C0444454.Definition: The right to obtain or make use of or take advantage of something (as services or membership); the right to enter. Also, an act or means of approaching.

C0087111.Name: Therapeutic procedure
C0087111.Definition: Procedures concerned with the remedial treatment or prevention of diseases.

C0205357.Name: Smooth
C0205357.Definition: Having a surface free from roughness or bumps or ridges or irregularities.

C0205134.Name: Curved
C0205134.Definition: A connected set of points constituting a one-dimensional continuum.

C0029468.Name: Osteotomy
C0029468.Definition: The surgical cutting of a bone. (Dorland, 28th ed)

C0001209.Name: Acromion
C0001209.Definition: The lateral extension of the spine of the SCAPULA and the highest point of the SHOULDER.

C1300196.Name: Organized
C1300196.Definition: The activity or result of distributing or disposing of things properly or methodically.

C0445204.Name: Preoperative
C0445204.Definition: Relating to or occurring during the period immediately before a surgical operation.

C0034014.Name: Bone structure of pubis
C0034014.Definition: A bone that forms the lower and anterior part of each side of the hip bone.

C0016068.Name: Fibula
C0016068.Definition: The bone of the lower leg lateral to and smaller than the tibia. In proportion to its length, it is the most slender of the long bones.

C4055506.Name: Accumulation
C4055506.Definition: A state characterized by the gradual increase in entities or substances.

C0439659.Name: Beginning
C0439659.Definition: The place where something begins or comes from in either the sense of a physical location or a metaphysical source.

C0040184.Name: Bone structure of tibia
C0040184.Definition: The second longest bone of the skeleton. It is located on the medial side of the lower leg, articulating with the FIBULA laterally, the TALUS distally, and the FEMUR proximally.

C0022130.Name: Islands
C0022130.Definition: A land mass smaller than a continent that is surrounded by water.

C0205390.Name: Phase
C0205390.Definition: A distinguishable part, a stage in a series of events or in a process of development, e.g. any of the varying aspects or stages in course of a disease; a fraction of a cycle.

C0036033.Name: Sacral Region
C0036033.Definition: The triangular bone, made up of 5 fused bones of the spine, located in the lower area of the spine between the fifth lumbar vertebra and the coccyx.

C1258215.Name: Ileus
C1258215.Definition: A condition caused by the lack of intestinal PERISTALSIS or INTESTINAL MOTILITY without any mechanical obstruction. This interference of the flow of INTESTINAL CONTENTS often leads to INTESTINAL OBSTRUCTION. Ileus may be classified into postoperative, inflammatory, metabolic, neurogenic, and drug-induced.
Aliases: bowel obstruction causing colic, vomiting, and constipation

C0031153.Name: Peritoneum
C0031153.Definition: A membrane of squamous EPITHELIAL CELLS, the mesothelial cells, covered by apical MICROVILLI that allow rapid absorption of fluid and particles in the PERITONEAL CAVITY. The peritoneum is divided into parietal and visceral components. The parietal peritoneum covers the inside of the ABDOMINAL WALL. The visceral peritoneum covers the intraperitoneal organs. The double-layered peritoneum forms the MESENTERY that suspends these organs from the abdominal wall.

C0013769.Name: Elbow
C0013769.Definition: Region of the body immediately surrounding and including the ELBOW JOINT.

C1455761.Name: Episodic
C1455761.Definition: Applied to a sign, symptom, or other manifestation that occurs multiple times at usually irregular intervals. The occurences are separated by an interval in which the sign, symptom, or manifestation is not present. []

C0011343.Name: Dental Cementum
C0011343.Definition: The bonelike rigid connective tissue covering the root of a tooth from the cementoenamel junction to the apex and lining the apex of the root canal, also assisting in tooth support by serving as attachment structures for the periodontal ligament. (Jablonski, Dictionary of Dentistry, 1992)

C0439611.Name: Preliminary
C0439611.Definition: **Description:**Indicates that a result is incomplete. There are further results to come. This maps to the 'active' state in the observation result status code.

C0184967.Name: Insertion of pack (procedure)
C0184967.Definition: The filling of a wound or cavity with gauze, sponge, or other material.

C0442030.Name: Parietal
C0442030.Definition: Of, or relating to, or associated with the parietal bones.

C0001807.Name: Aggressive behavior
C0001807.Definition: Behavior which may be manifested by destructive and attacking action which is verbal or physical, by covert attitudes of hostility or by obstructionism.

C1253959.Name: Branch of
C1253959.Definition: A part of a forking structure; a division or offshoot from a main stem.

C0029456.Name: Osteoporosis
C0029456.Definition: Reduction of bone mass without alteration in the composition of bone, leading to fractures. Primary osteoporosis can be of two major types: postmenopausal osteoporosis (OSTEOPOROSIS, POSTMENOPAUSAL) and age-related or senile osteoporosis.

C0003962.Name: Ascites
C0003962.Definition: Accumulation or retention of free fluid within the peritoneal cavity.
Aliases: accumulation of fluid in the abdomen

C0439855.Name: Complex
C0439855.Definition: Hard, involved or complicated, elaborate, having many parts.

C0442145.Name: Paraspinal
C0442145.Definition: Pertaining to muscles and/or tissue adjacent to the spinal column.

C1704972.Name: Genomic Orientation
C1704972.Definition: The orientation of a genomic element on the double stranded molecule.

C0680251.Name: Exclusion Criteria
C0680251.Definition: Medical and/or social characteristics that prevent a subject from being allowed to participate in a clinical study, as outlined in the study protocol.

C0205417.Name: Lobular
C0205417.Definition: Of or relating to or resembling a lobule.

C0000833.Name: Abscess
C0000833.Definition: Accumulation of purulent material in tissues, organs, or circumscribed spaces, usually associated with signs of infection.

C0277814.Name: Sitting position
C0277814.Definition: The state or act of one who sits; the posture of one who occupies a seat.

C0037253.Name: Skeletal system
C0037253.Definition: The collection of bones and tissues, including ligaments and cartilage, that compose the rigid internal framework of the human body, and which serves a multitude of functions, including structural support, movement, protection, production of blood cells, storage of ions, and endocrine regulation.

C1280412.Name: Thick
C1280412.Definition: Wide in width, extent or cross-section.

C0205092.Name: Unilateral
C0205092.Definition: Involving only one part or side.

C2698651.Name: Optimum
C2698651.Definition: The best or most suitable; the greatest degree attainable.

C2699029.Name: Relocation of home or business
C2699029.Definition: The act of changing your residence or place of business.

C0021308.Name: Infarction
C0021308.Definition: Formation of an infarct, which is NECROSIS in tissue due to local ISCHEMIA resulting from obstruction of BLOOD CIRCULATION, most commonly by a THROMBUS or EMBOLUS.

C0181904.Name: Monitor Device
C0181904.Definition: A device than includes a sensor designed to give information about the presence of a substance or the state of a system.

C0337088.Name: Electrical battery
C0337088.Definition: Power supplies consisting of a set of electrochemical cells designed to store chemical energy and release it in the form of electrical power; the cells are usually connected in series. Single electrochemical cells used as electric power sources are also commonly called batteries. Every cell, regardless of its chemical composition, consists of a negative electrode, a positive electrode, an ionic conducting material (electrolyte), a separator to electrically isolate the electrodes, and a case; the electric current flows externally from the positive to the negative electrode . Batteries are usually described by some characteristic of their chemical composition (e.g., nickel-cadmium, zinc-carbon, lithium); they may be nonrechargeable (i.e., a primary battery) or rechargeable (i.e., a secondary battery). Batteries are mostly used in the field of medicine as power supplies for implantable medical devices (e.g., pacemakers, neural stimulators) and external medical instruments (e.g., defibrillators, pacemaker programmers), for backup power for programmable devices that must retain electronic information, and in portable or other medical devices when it is not possible or convenient to use the line supply.

C0017480.Name: Germany
C0017480.Definition: A country in central Europe, bordering the Baltic Sea and the North Sea, between the Netherlands and Poland, south of Denmark. The capital is Berlin.

C1282573.Name: Evacuation procedure
C1282573.Definition: Removal of the contents of a body cavity or container

C0444467.Name: Thoracoabdominal
C0444467.Definition: Relating to, involving, or affecting the thorax and abdomen.

C4527217.Name: Infiltrative Tumor Margin
C4527217.Definition: Describes a tumor border that is invading the adjacent tissue.

C0231303.Name: Distress
C0231303.Definition: A state of physiological or psychological stress that cannot be compensated for by normal adaptive measures.

C0015733.Name: Feces
C0015733.Definition: Excrement from the INTESTINES, containing unabsorbed solids, waste products, secretions, and BACTERIA of the DIGESTIVE SYSTEM.

C0006104.Name: Brain
C0006104.Definition: The part of CENTRAL NERVOUS SYSTEM that is contained within the skull (CRANIUM). Arising from the NEURAL TUBE, the embryonic brain is comprised of three major parts including PROSENCEPHALON (the forebrain); MESENCEPHALON (the midbrain); and RHOMBENCEPHALON (the hindbrain). The developed brain consists of CEREBRUM; CEREBELLUM; and other structures in the BRAIN STEM.

C0007226.Name: Cardiovascular system
C0007226.Definition: The HEART and the BLOOD VESSELS by which BLOOD is pumped and circulated through the body.

C0041296.Name: Tuberculosis
C0041296.Definition: Any of the infectious diseases of man and other animals caused by species of MYCOBACTERIUM TUBERCULOSIS.

C0007634.Name: Cells
C0007634.Definition: The fundamental, structural, and functional units or subunits of living organisms. They are composed of CYTOPLASM containing various ORGANELLES and a CELL MEMBRANE boundary.
